From 7bc2bd1e1fa27333604774131cb07477a98026da Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Z User <z@container>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 22:21:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: restore home page, fix auth sync FK crash, harden admin
 arrays

CRITICAL FIXES (on top of previous session's work)

1. HOME PAGE WAS SHOWING ADMIN SETTINGS (CRITICAL)
   - Root cause: commit aef89ce accidentally replaced src/app/page.tsx
     (the home page) with the admin SettingsView component.
   - Every visitor to glamonepal.com saw the admin settings page, which
     called /api/v1/settings (admin-only) and got 401 errors.
   - Fix: restored the original home page with HeroBanner, ShopByCategory,
     FeaturedProducts, BrandPhilosophyBanner, BestSellers, etc.

2. AUTH SYNC FOREIGN KEY CONSTRAINT FAILURE (ROOT CAUSE OF ALL 401s)
   - Root cause: findOrCreateUser() tried to UPDATE users SET id = ? to
     change the primary key from the DB UUID to the Firebase UID when a
     user existed by email. This failed with
     SQLITE_CONSTRAINT: FOREIGN KEY constraint failed because cart,
     wishlist, orders, reviews, addresses, etc. all reference users(id).
   - This 500 error cascaded to ALL authenticated endpoints:
     /auth/me, /cart, /wishlist, /orders, /account/addresses all 401.
   - Fix: instead of changing the primary key, UPDATE the existing user's
     profile fields (first_name, last_name, email_verified) and return
     them AS-IS. The middleware already uses the DB user ID (not the
     Firebase UID) for authenticated requests, so all FK references
     remain valid.

3. RETURNS ENDPOINT 404
   - Root cause: returnRoutes.use('*', authMiddleware, requireRole) made
     ALL return operations admin-only, including customer-created returns.
   - Fix: POST /returns now only requires authMiddleware (customers can
     create returns for their own orders). GET and PATCH remain admin-only.

4. (l ?? []).map CRASH ON ALL ADMIN PAGES
   - Root cause: ?? [] only falls back on null/undefined. If the backend
     returns a non-array value (e.g. a number), it passes through and
     .map() throws.
   - Fix: replaced ?? [] with toArray() in DashboardView, AdminNotifications,
     and ProductQualityChecklist. toArray() always returns a real array.

5. SETUP WIZARD STILL EXISTS (DESPITE PREVIOUS 'REMOVAL')
   - The previous commit message said 'chore: remove setup wizard' but
     the files were still present. Now actually deleted.

VERIFICATION
- Frontend typecheck: 0 errors
- Backend typecheck: 0 errors
- Frontend build: 137/137 pages generated
